        <h1>LeetCode 3227: Vowels Game in a String (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Alice and Bob play a turn-based game on string s. Alice goes first. On Alice's turn, she removes any non-empty substring with odd number of vowels. On Bob's turn, he removes any non-empty substring with even number of vowels. The player who cannot make a move loses. Both play optimally. Return true if Alice wins.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: s = "leetcode" → Output: true. The string has 4 vowels (even). Alice can remove substring with 3 vowels, leaving 1 vowel. Bob needs even vowels but only 1 remains (odd), so Bob cannot move. Alice wins.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    bool doesAliceWin(string s) {
        // Key insight: Alice wins if and only if there's at least one vowel
        
        // The strategy is based on the total vowel count:
        // - If 0 vowels: Alice can't move (needs odd), Bob wins
        // - If odd vowels: Alice takes all vowels in one move, wins instantly  
        // - If even vowels: Alice takes (total-1) vowels, leaves 1 vowel
        //   Bob needs even vowels but only 1 remains (odd), Bob can't move
        
        const string VOWELS = "aeiou";
        
        // Check if any character in the string is a vowel
        for (char c : s) {
            if (VOWELS.find(c) != string::npos) {
                return true;  // Alice wins - at least one vowel exists
            }
        }
        
        return false;  // No vowels found - Alice cannot make any move, Bob wins
    }
};</code></pre>
